title: Horses die in consecutive races at Belmont Park after history-making event
description: Horses died in consecutive races at Belmont Park, dealing more untimely blows to the beleaguered sport, which had little time to celebrate its most uplifting events of the year.

title: How the Florida judge overseeing Trump's trial could hobble the Justice Department's case
description: A Trump appointee who has previously ruled in his favor will preside over a trial that could undermine public trust in the fairness of the court system for years to come.

title: Republicans downplay indictment as Trump team previews defense case ahead of arraignment
description: Republicans downplay indictment as Trump team previews defense case ahead of arraignment

title: Elevated section of Philadelphia I-95 collapses after  tanker truck bursts into flames
description: A massive tanker truck fire forced the closure of a section of Interstate Highway 95 in northeast Philadelphia after an elevated portion of the roadway collapsed, officials said Sunday morning.

title: Shoppers are flocking to Temu for cheap deals — but will the novelty last?
description: A pair of running shoes for $11.98.

title: What happened to the common cold? Post-Covid, it feels like every sniffle needs a name.
description: What virus is causing your cold? Is it RSV, rhinovirus, or something else? Experts say that in most cases, it doesn't matter what the virus is because the treatment is the same.

title: China has been spying on the U.S. from Cuba for years, Biden administration official says
description: China has long spied on the U.S. from Cuba, said an administration official. A Wall Street Journal story had said there was a new eavesdropping deal between China and Cuba.

title: Arcangelo takes Belmont Stakes, first woman-trained horse to win a Triple Crown race
description: Jena Antonucci became the first female trainer to win a Triple Crown race, as her colt Arcangelo won the Belmont Stakes on Saturday and brought down the curtain on a tumultuous five-week span of racing.
